message.content: It is not possible to provide a definitive answer as opinions on divorce can vary greatly among women in Canada. However, it can be said that attitudes towards divorce have evolved over time. Many women in Canada view divorce as a viable option to end an unhappy or unhealthy marriage. They may see it as a means to regain their independence, pursue personal growth, or prioritize their own well-being. However, it is important to note that individual perspectives on divorce can differ based on cultural, religious, and personal beliefs.
